LEGAL AUTO CLAIMS INSURANCE POLICY

This Legal Auto Claims Insurance Policy (the ?Policy?) is hereby issued and entered into as of June 29, 1988 (?Effective Date?), between Geico (?Insurer?) and Kelly Armstrong (?Insured?). This Policy will remain in force until the termination date of August 16, 1992 (?Expiration Date?). The policy number for this Legal Auto Claims Policy is 7e98a82c-0011-4619-80af-d2efc4b0ba4e, and the premium amount for this policy is $482,830. 

I. AUTOMOBILE LIABILITY INSURANCE

A. Coverage

This section of the policy provides coverage for bodily injury and property damage arising from the ownership, maintenance, or use of any insured automobile. 

B. Exclusions

This coverage does not apply to:

1. Bodily injury or property damage caused intentionally by the insured.
2. Bodily injury or property damage caused by the insured while driving under the influence of drugs or alcohol.
3. Bodily injury or property damage caused by the insured while driving a vehicle that is not listed on the policy.

LIMITS OF LIABILITY:
The maximum amount that the Insurer will pay for any one accident is $100,000 for bodily injury to or death of one person, $300,000 for bodily injury to or death of two or more persons, and $50,000 for property damage.

WHAT IS NOT COVERED:
The Insurer will not pay for:

1. Bodily injury or property damage caused by war, invasion, or insurrection.
2. Bodily injury or property damage caused by the use of nuclear weapons.
3. Bodily injury or property damage caused by pollution or contamination.

II. AUTOMOBILE MEDICAL PAYMENTS

A. Coverage

This section of the policy provides coverage for necessary medical and funeral expenses incurred by the insured, relatives of the insured, or occupants of the insured automobile as a result of an accident.

B. Exclusions

This coverage does not apply to:

1. Expenses incurred while the insured is riding in a vehicle owned by the insured but not listed on the policy.
2. Expenses incurred while the insured is operating a vehicle borrowed from another person.

LIMITS OF LIABILITY:
The maximum amount that the Insurer will pay for any one accident is $5,000.

WHAT IS NOT COVERED:
The Insurer will not pay for:

1. Expenses incurred while the insured is driving a vehicle for business purposes.
2. Expenses incurred while the insured is driving a vehicle for racing or speed contests.
3. Expenses incurred while the insured is driving a vehicle outside the United States or Canada.

III. AUTOMOBILE DEBT INDEMNITY INSURANCE

A. Coverage

This section of the policy provides coverage for the balance of any loan or lease outstanding on the insured automobile in the event of total loss or theft.

B. Exclusions

This coverage does not apply to:

1. Total loss or theft caused by the insured?s intentional acts.
2. Total loss or theft caused by the insured?s negligence.

LIMITS OF LIABILITY:
The maximum amount that the Insurer will pay for any one accident is the balance of the loan or lease outstanding on the insured automobile.

WHAT IS NOT COVERED:
The Insurer will not pay for:

1. Total loss or theft caused by war, invasion, or insurrection.
2. Total loss or theft caused by the use of nuclear weapons.
3. Total loss or theft caused by pollution or contamination.

IV. UNINSURED MOTORISTS INSURANCE

A. Coverage

This section of the policy provides coverage for bodily injury to the insured, relatives of the insured, or occupants of the insured automobile caused by an uninsured motorist.

B. Exclusions

This coverage does not apply to:

1. Bodily injury caused while the insured is operating a vehicle borrowed from another person.
2. Bodily injury caused while the insured is driving a vehicle for business purposes.

LIMITS OF LIABILITY:
The maximum amount that the Insurer will pay for any one accident is $100,000 for bodily injury to or death of one person, $300,000 for bodily injury to or death of two or more persons.

WHAT IS NOT COVERED:
The Insurer will not pay for:

1. Bodily injury caused intentionally by the insured.
2. Bodily injury caused by the insured while driving under the influence of drugs or alcohol.

V. DEFAULT PROVISIONS

A. Cancellation

This policy may be cancelled by either party upon 30 days? written
